meta.description:
[The Latest NGA COVID-19 situation report is now available].

This phylogeny shows evolutionary relationships of SARS-CoV-2 viruses from the ongoing novel coronavirus COVID-19 pandemic with an extra focus on "reinfected cases". This phylogeny shows an initial emergence in Wuhan, China, in Nov-Dec 2019 followed by sustained human-to-human transmission leading to sampled infections. Although the genetic relationships among sampled viruses are quite clear, there is considerable uncertainty surrounding estimates of specific transmission dates and in reconstruction of geographic spread.

Because it becomes harder to vizualize several thousands of genomes at once with such internet based application, we also made smaller subsamples available for easier and faster analysis focused on a particular databse and/or focus. They are available on the \"Dataset\" dropdown on the left from either GISAID or GENBANK repositories.

On the other hand, if you desire to analyze all existing available samples, just click on All; it may take several minutes to upload the whole dataset. Keep in mind that some subtle trends may not be visible in smaller subsampled dataset.

Site numbering and genome structure uses [Wuhan-Hu-1/2019](https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/nuccore/MN908947) as reference. The phylogeny is rooted relative to early samples from Wuhan. Multiple genomic sequence alignment is performed by the Multiple Alignment using Fast Fourier Transform [MAFFT algorithm v7.471](https://mafft.cbrc.jp/alignment/software/). The Phylogenetic tree inference relied on Maximum Likelihood inference from [IQ-TREE v2.0.3](http://www.iqtree.org/) and [TreeTime algorithm v0.7.4](https://treetime.readthedocs.io/en/latest/). Finally, We made no pre-assumption for the nucleotide substitution rate per site per year; it is estimated from our largest samples available by [least-squares regression by TreeTime](https://treetime.readthedocs.io/en/latest/tutorials/clock.html). For further details on the [bioinformatic processing with AUGUR](https://nextstrain-augur.readthedocs.io/en/stable/), including genomic masking and filtering, please contact NGA Data Corps, DCD-Intel, [Dr. Sebastien Dartevelle](mailto:sebastien.dartevelle@nga.mil).

We gratefully acknowledge the authors, originating and submitting laboratories of the genetic sequence and metadata made available through [GISAID](https://gisaid.org) and [GenBank](https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/genbank/).

PhyloDynamic and PhyloGeographic Bioinformatics, Visualization, and Analytics are maintained by [NGA](https://www.nga.mil), Data Corps, DCD-Intel Branch, [Dr. Sebastien Dartevelle](mailto:sebastien.dartevelle@nga.mil) in collaboration with NGA Research Predictive Analytics and the US NAVY's Naval Medical Research Center [NMRC](https://www.med.navy.mil/sites/nmrc/NMRC/Pages/NMRC.aspx)/[Biological Defense Research Directorate](https://www.med.navy.mil/sites/nmrc/NMRC/NMRC_Offices/Pages/BDRD.aspx). Bioinformatic modeling is performed on the [Department of Defense High Performance Computing Systems](https://www.hpc.mil/) to which we express herewith our gratitude to the entire DOD HPC team for their support, service, help, kindness, and patience.

For any visualization and/or modeling special request, please, [email us](mailto:sebastien.dartevelle@nga.mil).
